"{\"uid\": \"nbcolympics.com-news-usas-miles-partain-andy-benesh-eliminated-olympic-beach-volleyball-tournament\", \"text\": \"AmericansMiles Partain/Andy Beneshfell to Qatar'sCherif Younousse/Ahmed Tijanin the quarterfinals (21-14, 21-16) and were eliminated from the men's beach volleyball tournament at Eiffel Tower Stadium on Wednesday.  As a result, no U.S. beach volleyball team, men's or women's, will win an Olympic medal for the first time ever.  Younousse/Tijan - Tokyo bronze medalists and one of the top-ranked defensive teams in the men's field - stifled the Americans' option offense that helped get them to the quarterfinals.  Partain/Benesh fought hard in the beginning of the first set. A four-point Qatari run put Younousse/Tijan up 11-8, but the U.S. responded with a 4-0 run of their own to take a 12-11 lead. Qatar then went on a 6-0 run to take a 17-12 lead and ended the set on a 10-2 run overall to comfortably win the first period of play.  Qatar wore out the U.S. in the second set, taking a lead and holding on for the straight sets victory. Partain/Benesh had promising moments throughout the match but could not build enough momentum to combat the sharp play of the Qataris.  Younousse/Tijan will face world No. 1 teamDavid Ahman/Jonatan Hellvigof Sweden, who they defeated earlier in the tournament.  MATCH STATSMEN'S BRACKET  Note: Some components ofNBCOlympics.commay not be optimized for users browsing with           Internet           Explorer 11, 10 or older browsers or systems.  A Division ofNBCUniversal  \\u00a9 2025 NBCUniversal. All rights reserved.Any use, reproduction, modification, distribution, display or performance of this material without NBCUniversal's prior written consent is prohibited.Use of the Website signifies your agreement to the Terms of Use and Privacy Policy.  \\u00a9IOC 2025 Official Results powered by Atos. Timing and results management by Omega.\"}"